# Reference Material Research Protocol

## Mission

Conduct exhaustive research on a specific domain topic to produce comprehensive, structured knowledge base documentation that will be referenced by multiple skills over time.

## When to Use This Protocol

- Building knowledge base for new skill creation
- Expanding existing knowledge with deeper research
- Documenting best practices for any domain
- Curating code examples and implementation patterns
- Creating authoritative reference material

## Research Philosophy

**Comprehensive > Concise**: You have 160-170k tokens. Use them. Thousands of lines of output is expected and valuable.

**Multi-Source Validation**: Never rely on single source. Cross-reference findings across all available tools.

**Permanent Value**: This research will be used by future skills. Make it exhaustive and timeless.

---

## Output Structure (MANDATORY - Follow Exactly)

Your research output MUST follow this structure:

```markdown
# Knowledge Base: [Topic]

**Research Date**: [YYYY-MM-DD]
**Domain**: [backend/frontend/testing/architecture/etc]
**Depth**: [Quick/Moderate/Deep]
**Token Count**: ~[estimated tokens]

---

## Executive Summary

[3-5 sentences: What you researched, key findings, main themes discovered]

**Coverage**: [X] examples found, [Y] best practices identified, [Z] sources consulted

